{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LQ8rVXczvGfmG2MXUNX7ZB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create my final report:\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: Bead UI Structure and Run Management\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the codebase, here are my findings:\n\n### 1. **Bead UI Structure**\n\nThe web UI is located in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/` with the following components:\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main HTTP handler (56.7 KB, contains API endpoints and page rendering)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/` - HTML templates:\n  - `layout.html` - Base layout wrapper\n  - `runs.html` - Runs list page with polling and grouping logic\n  - `project_detail.html` - Project page showing workflows, recent runs\n  - `run_detail.html` - Individual run detail with steps, logs, child runs\n  - `projects.html` - Projects listing page\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - 605-line stylesheet with comprehensive theming\n\n### 2. **How Runs Are Currently Displayed**\n\n**On the Runs Page (`/runs`):**\n- Template: `runs.html`\n- Handler: `handleRunsList()` at line 255 of handler.go\n- Data passed: All runs (or filtered by project), project list for filtering\n- Table columns: Run ID, Title, Project, Workflow, Type, State, Timing, Container, Error\n- CSS classes for styling: `run-parent-row` (de-emphasized at 0.7 opacity), `run-child-row` (indented with leader character)\n\n**JavaScript Grouping (runs.html lines 85-136):**\n```javascript\nfunction groupRuns(runs) {\n  // Groups runs by parent-child relationship\n  // Children immediately follow their parent\n  // Top-level runs sorted by: running first, then by started_at descending\n  // Returns array of {run, isParent, isChild} objects\n}\n```\n\n**On the Project Page (`/projects/{name}`):**\n- Template: `project_detail.html`\n- Handler: `handleProjectDetail()` \n- Shows: Recent 10 runs as colored dots representing run states\n- Displays: Project info (docker image, version, prompt files), workflows with DAG visualization\n- Workflow tabs: Distinguishes between \"Container\" and \"Host\" workflows\n\n**On Run Detail Page (`/runs/{id}`):**\n- Template: `run_detail.html`\n- Handler: `handleRunDetail()` at line 398 of handler.go\n- Shows: Run metadata, child runs table, steps table with result badges, live log viewer\n- Child runs section: Lists all container runs dispatched from this host run\n- Live updates via SSE (Server-Sent Events): `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n\n### 3. **Task-to-Run Relationships**\n\n**Domain Types:**\n\nFrom `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`:\n```go\ntype Task struct {\n  ID          string\n  Status      string  // \"open\", \"closed\", \"in-progress\"\n  Title       string\n  Description string\n  Metadata    map[string]string\n}\n\ntype TaskAssignment struct {\n  AssignedAt time.Time\n  RunID      string  // run ID handling this task (set after main completes)\n}\n\ntype TaskStateEntry struct {\n  Task       Task\n  Assigned   bool\n  AssignedAt time.Time\n  RunID      string  // empty if not yet known\n}\n```\n\nFrom `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 73-88):\n```go\ntype TaskEntry struct {\n  ID          string\n  Status      string\n  Title       string\n  Description string\n  Metadata    map[string]string\n  Assigned    bool\n  AssignedAt  string\n  RunID       string  // Links task to the run handling it\n}\n\ntype TaskProvider interface {\n  GetLoopTasks(projectDir string) []TaskEntry\n}\n```\n\n**Web API Endpoint:**\n- `/api/projects/{name}/tasks` - Returns array of TaskEntry with assignment state\n- Handler: `handleAPITasks()` at line 1401 of handler.go\n- Returns: JSON array of tasks with `assigned`, `assigned_at`, `run_id` fields\n\n### 4. **Understanding \"list-tasks\", \"main\", \"develop\", \"finalize\" Run Types**\n\n**Host Workflows (from `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`):**\n\nThree-phase orchestration model in `.cloche/host.cloche`:\n\n| Phase | Workflow Name | Type | Purpose |\n|-------|--------------|------|---------|\n| 1 | `list-tasks` | Host workflow | Discover available work; output is JSONL |\n| 2 | `main` | Host workflow | Do the work; receives `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var |\n| 3 | `finalize` | Host workflow | Post-main cleanup; runs on both success/failure |\n\n**Container Workflows:**\n- Named workflows in `.cloche/*.cloche` files (e.g., `develop.cloche`, `custom.cloche`)\n- Example from `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche`: A workflow named \"develop\" with steps: implement → test → lint/quality → fix\n- Dispatched via `workflow_name` step type in host workflows\n- Run as child runs (with `ParentRunID` set) from host orchestration runs\n\n**Run Domain Type** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` lines 31-47):\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n  ID           string\n  WorkflowName string  // Name of the workflow executed (\"main\", \"develop\", \"list-tasks\", etc.)\n  State        RunState\n  IsHost       bool    // true for host workflow runs\n  ParentRunID  string  // empty for top-level, set to host run ID for container runs\n  Title        string  // One-line summary\n  ProjectDir   string\n  ContainerID  string  // Docker container ID\n  StartedAt    time.Time\n  CompletedAt  time.Time\n  StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n}\n```\n\n### 5. **Existing Grouping Logic**\n\n**Parent-Child Grouping by `ParentRunID`:**\n- Location: `runs.html` template, JavaScript `groupRuns()` function (lines 85-136)\n- Logic: Groups container runs under their parent host run\n- Visual effect: Parent rows de-emphasized (0.7 opacity), child rows indented with leader character \"└ \"\n- Sorting: Top-level runs sorted by state (running first) then by `started_at` descending\n- CSS: `.run-parent-row` and `.run-child-row` classes (lines 576-582 of style.css)\n\n**Data Flow:**\n1. `handleAPIRuns()` fetches all runs and converts to `apiRun` JSON\n2. `toAPIRun()` preserves `ParentRunID` field (line 485)\n3. Client-side JavaScript fetches JSON via `/api/runs` and groups before rendering\n\n### 6. **Task-Related Grouping UI Elements**\n\n**Web Handler Task Support:**\n- `TaskProvider` interface at handler.go line 86\n- `WithTaskProvider()` option to configure task provider\n- `handleAPITasks()` endpoint returns task state with run IDs\n- Test: `handler_test.go` lines 1775-1837 show task structure with `assigned`, `assigned_at`, `run_id` fields\n\n**Task State Tracking:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`:\n  - `taskRuns` map: task ID → `TaskAssignment` (lines 82, 99, 120)\n  - `GetTaskSnapshot()` method (lines 273-305): Returns current task state with assignment info\n  - Task deduplication via timeout window (5 minutes default, configurable)\n\n### 7. **Key Files to Understand Runs**\n\n**Domain:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run, RunState, StepExecution types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow, Step, Wiring definitions\n\n**Web UI:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - All HTTP handlers and data transformations\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list with grouping logic\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail, child runs, live logs\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Styling for parent/child rows\n\n**Orchestration/Loops:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Three-phase orchestration loop, task assignment\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` - Task domain types and TaskAssigner interface\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - How named workflows (list-tasks, main, finalize) are executed\n\n**Ports:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - RunStore interface for persistence\n\n### 8. **Run Type Classification Determination**\n\nRuns are classified by:\n1. **`IsHost` field**: true = host orchestration run, false = container workflow run\n2. **`WorkflowName` field**: The specific workflow executed (\"main\", \"list-tasks\", \"develop\", etc.)\n3. **`ParentRunID` field**: If set, this is a child run dispatched from a host run\n4. **Relationship to tasks**: Task ID passed via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var; run ID tracked in task assignment state\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** The Bead UI uses a parent-child run grouping pattern where host orchestration runs serve as \"parents\" and container workflow dispatches are \"children\". Tasks are optional and create an additional dimension: tasks are discovered via `list-tasks` phase, assigned to `main` phase runs, and tracked through the task pipeline with assignment timestamps and run IDs. The existing grouping focuses on run hierarchy; task grouping would add semantic organization around work items vs. workflow invocations."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a598ebfd4c908bdca (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 77516\ntool_uses: 43\nduration_ms: 201129</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f295beb-8c86-4874-b68a-30cd91542139","uuid":"acc0702e-cb9e-40e9-a598-48dbb16e2d56","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The Bead UI structure - find all UI-related files (templates, handlers, routes, etc.)\n2. How runs are currently displayed on the Runs page\n3. How runs are currently displayed on the Project page\n4. How tasks relate to runs (look at domain types for Run, Task, etc.)\n5. What \"list-tasks\" runs look like vs main/develop/finalize runs\n6. Any existing grouping logic\n\nLook for:\n- HTML templates (*.html, *.tmpl, *.gohtml)\n- UI handlers/routes\n- Domain types for Run and Task\n- Any existing task-related grouping\n\nBe very thorough - check all relevant directories including internal/, cmd/, and any web/ui directories.","agentId":"a598ebfd4c908bdca","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create my final report:\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: Bead UI Structure and Run Management\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the codebase, here are my findings:\n\n### 1. **Bead UI Structure**\n\nThe web UI is located in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/` with the following components:\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main HTTP handler (56.7 KB, contains API endpoints and page rendering)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/` - HTML templates:\n  - `layout.html` - Base layout wrapper\n  - `runs.html` - Runs list page with polling and grouping logic\n  - `project_detail.html` - Project page showing workflows, recent runs\n  - `run_detail.html` - Individual run detail with steps, logs, child runs\n  - `projects.html` - Projects listing page\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - 605-line stylesheet with comprehensive theming\n\n### 2. **How Runs Are Currently Displayed**\n\n**On the Runs Page (`/runs`):**\n- Template: `runs.html`\n- Handler: `handleRunsList()` at line 255 of handler.go\n- Data passed: All runs (or filtered by project), project list for filtering\n- Table columns: Run ID, Title, Project, Workflow, Type, State, Timing, Container, Error\n- CSS classes for styling: `run-parent-row` (de-emphasized at 0.7 opacity), `run-child-row` (indented with leader character)\n\n**JavaScript Grouping (runs.html lines 85-136):**\n```javascript\nfunction groupRuns(runs) {\n  // Groups runs by parent-child relationship\n  // Children immediately follow their parent\n  // Top-level runs sorted by: running first, then by started_at descending\n  // Returns array of {run, isParent, isChild} objects\n}\n```\n\n**On the Project Page (`/projects/{name}`):**\n- Template: `project_detail.html`\n- Handler: `handleProjectDetail()` \n- Shows: Recent 10 runs as colored dots representing run states\n- Displays: Project info (docker image, version, prompt files), workflows with DAG visualization\n- Workflow tabs: Distinguishes between \"Container\" and \"Host\" workflows\n\n**On Run Detail Page (`/runs/{id}`):**\n- Template: `run_detail.html`\n- Handler: `handleRunDetail()` at line 398 of handler.go\n- Shows: Run metadata, child runs table, steps table with result badges, live log viewer\n- Child runs section: Lists all container runs dispatched from this host run\n- Live updates via SSE (Server-Sent Events): `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n\n### 3. **Task-to-Run Relationships**\n\n**Domain Types:**\n\nFrom `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`:\n```go\ntype Task struct {\n  ID          string\n  Status      string  // \"open\", \"closed\", \"in-progress\"\n  Title       string\n  Description string\n  Metadata    map[string]string\n}\n\ntype TaskAssignment struct {\n  AssignedAt time.Time\n  RunID      string  // run ID handling this task (set after main completes)\n}\n\ntype TaskStateEntry struct {\n  Task       Task\n  Assigned   bool\n  AssignedAt time.Time\n  RunID      string  // empty if not yet known\n}\n```\n\nFrom `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 73-88):\n```go\ntype TaskEntry struct {\n  ID          string\n  Status      string\n  Title       string\n  Description string\n  Metadata    map[string]string\n  Assigned    bool\n  AssignedAt  string\n  RunID       string  // Links task to the run handling it\n}\n\ntype TaskProvider interface {\n  GetLoopTasks(projectDir string) []TaskEntry\n}\n```\n\n**Web API Endpoint:**\n- `/api/projects/{name}/tasks` - Returns array of TaskEntry with assignment state\n- Handler: `handleAPITasks()` at line 1401 of handler.go\n- Returns: JSON array of tasks with `assigned`, `assigned_at`, `run_id` fields\n\n### 4. **Understanding \"list-tasks\", \"main\", \"develop\", \"finalize\" Run Types**\n\n**Host Workflows (from `/workspace/docs/workflows.md`):**\n\nThree-phase orchestration model in `.cloche/host.cloche`:\n\n| Phase | Workflow Name | Type | Purpose |\n|-------|--------------|------|---------|\n| 1 | `list-tasks` | Host workflow | Discover available work; output is JSONL |\n| 2 | `main` | Host workflow | Do the work; receives `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var |\n| 3 | `finalize` | Host workflow | Post-main cleanup; runs on both success/failure |\n\n**Container Workflows:**\n- Named workflows in `.cloche/*.cloche` files (e.g., `develop.cloche`, `custom.cloche`)\n- Example from `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche`: A workflow named \"develop\" with steps: implement → test → lint/quality → fix\n- Dispatched via `workflow_name` step type in host workflows\n- Run as child runs (with `ParentRunID` set) from host orchestration runs\n\n**Run Domain Type** (`/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` lines 31-47):\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n  ID           string\n  WorkflowName string  // Name of the workflow executed (\"main\", \"develop\", \"list-tasks\", etc.)\n  State        RunState\n  IsHost       bool    // true for host workflow runs\n  ParentRunID  string  // empty for top-level, set to host run ID for container runs\n  Title        string  // One-line summary\n  ProjectDir   string\n  ContainerID  string  // Docker container ID\n  StartedAt    time.Time\n  CompletedAt  time.Time\n  StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n}\n```\n\n### 5. **Existing Grouping Logic**\n\n**Parent-Child Grouping by `ParentRunID`:**\n- Location: `runs.html` template, JavaScript `groupRuns()` function (lines 85-136)\n- Logic: Groups container runs under their parent host run\n- Visual effect: Parent rows de-emphasized (0.7 opacity), child rows indented with leader character \"└ \"\n- Sorting: Top-level runs sorted by state (running first) then by `started_at` descending\n- CSS: `.run-parent-row` and `.run-child-row` classes (lines 576-582 of style.css)\n\n**Data Flow:**\n1. `handleAPIRuns()` fetches all runs and converts to `apiRun` JSON\n2. `toAPIRun()` preserves `ParentRunID` field (line 485)\n3. Client-side JavaScript fetches JSON via `/api/runs` and groups before rendering\n\n### 6. **Task-Related Grouping UI Elements**\n\n**Web Handler Task Support:**\n- `TaskProvider` interface at handler.go line 86\n- `WithTaskProvider()` option to configure task provider\n- `handleAPITasks()` endpoint returns task state with run IDs\n- Test: `handler_test.go` lines 1775-1837 show task structure with `assigned`, `assigned_at`, `run_id` fields\n\n**Task State Tracking:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`:\n  - `taskRuns` map: task ID → `TaskAssignment` (lines 82, 99, 120)\n  - `GetTaskSnapshot()` method (lines 273-305): Returns current task state with assignment info\n  - Task deduplication via timeout window (5 minutes default, configurable)\n\n### 7. **Key Files to Understand Runs**\n\n**Domain:**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run, RunState, StepExecution types\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Workflow, Step, Wiring definitions\n\n**Web UI:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - All HTTP handlers and data transformations\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list with grouping logic\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run detail, child runs, live logs\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - Styling for parent/child rows\n\n**Orchestration/Loops:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Three-phase orchestration loop, task assignment\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` - Task domain types and TaskAssigner interface\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - How named workflows (list-tasks, main, finalize) are executed\n\n**Ports:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - RunStore interface for persistence\n\n### 8. **Run Type Classification Determination**\n\nRuns are classified by:\n1. **`IsHost` field**: true = host orchestration run, false = container workflow run\n2. **`WorkflowName` field**: The specific workflow executed (\"main\", \"list-tasks\", \"develop\", etc.)\n3. **`ParentRunID` field**: If set, this is a child run dispatched from a host run\n4. **Relationship to tasks**: Task ID passed via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var; run ID tracked in task assignment state\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** The Bead UI uses a parent-child run grouping pattern where host orchestration runs serve as \"parents\" and container workflow dispatches are \"children\". Tasks are optional and create an additional dimension: tasks are discovered via `list-tasks` phase, assigned to `main` phase runs, and tracked through the task pipeline with assignment timestamps and run IDs. The existing grouping focuses on run hierarchy; task grouping would add semantic organization around work items vs. workflow invocations."}],"totalDurationMs":201129,"totalTokens":77516,"totalToolUseCount":43,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2641,"cache_read_input_tokens":72468,"output_tokens":2407,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2641},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
