{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TCbyr2Cp5Te4iy8h6VA6U5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to understand how tasks relate to runs. The key insight is:\n\n1. `TaskID` is set on the host executor/runner, not on the domain `Run` struct\n2. When a task is assigned, the orchestration loop calls `runWorkflow` with the task ID\n3. The task ID gets passed via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var to scripts\n4. The task assignment tracks `RunID` in `TaskAssignment`\n\nSo there's currently no `TaskID` field on the `Run` domain type. I need to:\n1. Add a `TaskID` field to `domain.Run`\n\n\n2. Store it when runs are created\n3. Include it in the API response\n4. Use it for grouping in the UI\n\nNow I'm checking how runs are stored in the SQLite schema, how the orchestration loop creates runs and passes task IDs, and what the handler test file shows about this flow.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4790,"cache_read_input_tokens":34500,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4790},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f295beb-8c86-4874-b68a-30cd91542139","uuid":"e201e260-d239-4285-965e-ec42385cca1f"}
